<br>
hunt around in your local n00b area till you get your lvl4 spells...<br>
<br>
head over to Butcherblock Mntns on Faydwer... <br>
I know, it's a bit to travel, especially if you're Erud like me, but usually getting to Qeynos is all you need... getting a ride from there is usually no problem...<br>
set up camp at the Crossroads section of BB... kill anything that you think you -can- kill... preferrably yellows and reds... <br>
once in a while you should head over to the druid ring and /con the skellies there... once they're yellow, start camping... these guys have great XP and decent loot... also, they're not within aggro range of each other so you will be able to take care of one at a time...  collect all bonechips you can lay your hands on... <br>
tip: there are 4 skellies around the ring and one &quot;secret&quot; skel... just south of the ring there's a small valley with a stone statue... looks like an ugly face... behind it there's another skellie... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     <br>
occasionally, head into Kaladim and go to the Paladin guild... there's a dorf there called Gunlok Jure... hand him 4 bonechips at a time (stacked is ok) and watch your XP and faction fly... XP is marvellous... repeat this till Gunloks XP is too low to be of any value... <br>
<br>
once the skellies start to go green and low blue, head over to Steamfont Mntns... locate the Mino cave... just beyond the Mino cave there are a bunch of gears (cogwheels) which are infested with more skellies... there are 5 of them, neatly placed so as to not interfere with each other... these guys will take you to 15 if you want, but the last level or two will seem like blah... <br>
<br>
at this point you might want to take a peak on the Chessboard in Butcherblock... if they give you nice XP, go keel them... <br>
<br>
the next step is Lavastorm... plenty of xp and loot there... kill Derv's and Drake's with the occasional elemental... avoid the imps and sprites... thems are nasty buggers... hits way harder than they /con... <br>
<br>
if you want to stay on Faydwer, head into Estate of Unrest... killing yardtrash is splendid xp and the loot is pretty good... <br>
my tip is to head to the right once inside... follow the right wall with the hedgemaze to your left until you come to the yard...  /pet guard here and go find stuff... Jack o Lantern's, Tormented Dead's and Death Beetles are all great xp and good enough loot with the occasional bronze weapon... <br>
the thing to note is to NOT panic when people shouts &quot;train&quot; (and believe me, they will)... the corner you're occupying is really quite safe... the backdoor to the mansion (where most pulls from the house is going on) is on the other side, making the opposite corner positivly lethal... you should have a small pagoda with a few undeads in it right next to you if you're in the right corner... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br>
<br>
at lvl16 you might want to consider heading over to Lake of Ill Omen (ignore Oasis)... really, I went from 18 to 24 in one session here... the XP is amazing... the thing about LoIO is that the majority of the players here are experienced groupers... getting a GOOD group is a breeze and once you're in one you'll see just how powerful organized grouping can be... you'll find yourself constantly nuking reds and hardly ever medding... hehe... it's weird, but true... believe me, you'll level like nobodys business... <br>
<br>
note on travelling... <br>
getting about is really not very hard... getting a port doesn't HAVE to cost 10pp... just be nice and ask and you'll find that more often than not you'll get a ride for free, buffs included... <br>
most importantly, don't be afraid to ask, and don't, ever, beg... seeing how I react to begging, I can understand that druids and wizzies have a short temper when it comes to begging... <br>
be respectful and you'll have a lot more fun... roleplaying to get a port is usually appreciated too... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     <br>
<br>
good luck. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uaphael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aphael</A> at: 7/20/01 5:53:25 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill>The Hunt</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM GAMES AD SCRIPT -->
